  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> has the following weapon enhancements:</p><p>Accuracy Scope. <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> gains a +2 to attack rolls (included). Amplifying Barrel. Specialist gains a +2 to damage (included). Bayonet. <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature} </span>can make melee attacks with the finesse property utilizing his sniper rifle.</p><p>Booming Strikes. Once per turn, when the <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> hits with the weapon, he can deal an additional 1d6 damage (included). The weapon makes a loud boom which can be heard 100 feet away. If the <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature} </span>is hidden, Intelligence (Investigation) and Wisdom (Perception) checks made to locate you that rely on sound have advantage.</p><p>Overcharge Weapon. The <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature} </span>can expend one tech slot to deal additional damage to the target. The extra damage is 1d6 for a 1st-level tech slot, plus 1d6 for each slot level higher than 1st, to a maximum of 5d6. The damage is the same type as the weapon damage. You can add this damage to the extra damage of your Booming Strikes.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
